data.name: Label4.Text
data.value:
Use the Simulator Form to practice trading chart patterns. In this example, the trader has selected a chart pattern to trade (highlighted at C), clicked Start, the simulator has advanced to the chart pattern, and paused. The trader has setup his trade details (B) such as shares and targets, and is ready to begin trading by clicking Resume (F). That’s the sequence of how to use the simulator.
The chart at A will appear after you start the simulator.
Click B for help with the trading controls.
Click the list box at C for a chart pattern you wish to trade. If none are listed, select the Patterns button on the right for a choice of chart patterns. The Setup button also allows you to select the scale you’re trading (daily/weekly/monthly). INTRADAY TRADES WILL BE SELECTED AUTOMATICALLY.
The slider at D determines how fast new price bars appear.
Label E shows new chart patterns or candle patterns as they are recognized. Click the Patterns or Candles button to select different patterns.
Use the buttons at F to start, pause, or resume a simulation.
At G, additional controls appear. Setup loads the Setup Form where additional options appear. Click < or > buttons to move to the previous or next security. Candles and Patterns allow the selection of patterns to view (candles) or trade (patterns).
Not shown, but to the left of the image is a list box showing details of completed trades. Also the Skip check box (above the previous/next button on lower left of form) will skip files not showing a selected chart pattern.
